\n< Prostitute >Ahh... I've been drinking too much lately...

\n< Prostitute >I love alcohol, and if I don't drink, I can't make
a living. Plus, it's more entertaining when I'm
drunk. But I know I won't have a good ending...

\n< Prostitute >If you don't know what to do, just drink some
alcohol and put on a fake smile. You can handle
anything that way. Plus, the payment is on their
end, so you get to drink for free. It's awesome,
right?

\n< Prostitute >Even if something unpleasant happens, if you're
drunk, it helps distract your mind, so you don't
have to feel as bad about it.

\n< Prostitute >But if you get too drunk, it can affect your work
afterwards, and you never know what might happen
if you're in a vulnerable state, so be careful.

\n< Prostitute >Some customers come expecting that, so they'll
make you drink alcohol. And the shop won't help
you unless it's to a certain extent.
\n< Prostitute >...In the end, I have to protect myself on my own.

\n< Prostitute >Oh my, a new colleague, I wonder. How cute... and
pitiful.

\n< Prostitute >For someone as cute as you, this job is easy. The
men who come to a place like this are
straightforward and if I let them do what they
want, they'll pay a lot of money.

\n< Prostitute >But that means accepting the act of pleasing the
other person using you. If you choose to do that,
you have to endure and accept unpleasant things.

\n< Prostitute >And endurance is poison. It's okay if it's just a
little, but if there's too much, it makes me feel
sick and I can't focus on my work.

\n< Prostitute >So, if there's something you really don't want to
do, it's better to have the courage to refuse. You
might receive less money and the client might not
like it and leave, but that's a possibility.

\n< Prostitute >But in the end, that's the way to work for a long
time. Taking it easy and steadily building up
without pushing yourself too hard, that's the
trick to this job, I guess?
